Spring Cloud Config Server is part of the Spring Cloud project â€” a suite of tools specifically designed for building and managing cloud-native applications.

It provides centralized external configuration management, backed by Git, file system, SVN, or even a database.
It can talk with Git, file system, SVN, or even a database to access configuration.


